<section>
  <h4>Part 7: Hello Bubbling</h4>
  <p>Event bubbling provides a way for child components to update their parents' state.</p>
  <div id="part7-app" class="demo"></div>

<div class="key-code">
<h6><i class="fa fa-code"></i> Key code</h6>
<script type="text/plain" class="language-jsx">// app.js
// Pass a parent component's update function down to its child
<ChildComponent
  options={data}
  changeAnimal={
    (animal) => this.setState({ animal: animal })
  }
/>
</script>
<script type="text/plain" class="language-jsx">// component.js
// The child can then call that function to update its parent!
<input
  type='radio'
  name='radio-options'
  onClick={() => {
    // ...
    props.changeAnimal(option);
  }}
/>
</script>
</div>
